This paper deals with graph theory and spectral graph theory, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The paper presents a new approach to bounding the mixing time of a graph, which is a central problem in computer science. The paper is likely to be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) because it deals with graph algorithms and combinatorial optimization. It could also be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) because it deals with network analysis and community detection. Additionally, the paper uses tools from information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and computational complexity (cs.CC), which are all relevant subfields of computer science.
